meta {
  name: Groq Chat Completions
  type: http
  seq: 4
}

post {
  url: https://api.groq.com/openai/v1/chat/completions
  body: json
  auth: none
}

headers {
  Authorization: Bearer {{GROQ_API_KEY}}
  Content-Type: application/json
}

body:json {
  {
    "model": "meta-llama/llama-4-scout-17b-16e-instruct",
    "max_tokens": 4096,
    "temperature": 0.3,
    "response_format": { "type": "json_object" },
    "messages": [
      {
        "role": "system",
        "content": "You are a daily standup parser for a developer productivity tool called Narada. Parse the user's daily update transcript and extract structured data.\n\nDate context: 2026-04-07\n\nInstructions:\n- Extract discrete work tasks with descriptions and any Jira issue keys mentioned (format: PROJ-1234)\n- Parse time references into durations in seconds (e.g., \"3 hours\" = 10800)\n- Detect blockers from natural speech\n- Extract tomorrow's planned tasks. If the user doesn't mention tomorrow, set tomorrowTasks to a single entry: \"Continue working on same tasks\"\n- For time entries, use the date \"2026-04-07\" combined with sequential start times beginning at 10:00. Each entry's \"started\" should be an ISO 8601 datetime string. Schedule entries sequentially — each entry starts when the previous one ends.\n- Set isRepeat to false for all entries you extract (repeat entries are handled separately)\n\nTime distribution rules:\n- The total time for non-repeat entries should be at least 28800 seconds (8.0h) to reach 8h total when combined with repeat entries\n- Minimum time per entry is 1800 seconds (30 minutes)\n- Round all time entries to the nearest 30-minute increment (1800s multiples)\n- If the user specifies exact times for tasks, use those values (rounded to nearest 30-min)\n- If the user does NOT specify exact times, infer relative weightage from each task's description\n\nOutput format for slackFormat (Slack mrkdwn):\n`TODAY`\n• TICKET-KEY : task description\n\n`TOMORROW`\n• TICKET-KEY : planned task description\n\n`BLOCKER`\n• blocker description\n(Use \"NA\" if no blockers mentioned)\n\nOutput format for teamsFormat (Teams markdown):\n**TODAY**\n- TICKET-KEY : task description\n\n**TOMORROW**\n- TICKET-KEY : planned task description\n\n**BLOCKER**\n- blocker description\n(Use \"NA\" if no blockers mentioned)\n\nRespond with a JSON object containing: tasks (array of {description, issueKey, timeEstimate}), blockers (array of strings), timeEntries (array of {issueKey, timeSpentSecs, started, comment, isRepeat}), tomorrowTasks (array of {description, issueKey}), slackFormat (string), teamsFormat (string)."
      },
      {
        "role": "user",
        "content": "Parse this daily update transcript:\n\nToday I worked on the NARADA-42 Groq integration for about 3 hours, adding the provider, settings UI, and API routes. Then spent 2 hours on NARADA-43 code review for the auth refactor. Had a quick 1 hour sync with the team about the release plan. Also did about 2 hours of NARADA-44 bug fixes in the calendar component. Tomorrow I'll continue with testing the Groq integration and start on the notification system. No blockers."
      }
    ]
  }
}

settings {
  encodeUrl: false
  timeout: 0
}

docs {
  # Groq Chat Completions (External)

  Direct call to the Groq Chat Completions API with the Narada system prompt.
  Validates both the API key and that the model returns correct structured JSON.

  Set `{{GROQ_API_KEY}}` in your Bruno environment.

  Note: The system prompt contains a hardcoded date (2026-04-07). Update it in the request body if testing date-sensitive behavior.

  ## What to verify
  1. Response returns 200
  2. JSON contains: tasks, blockers, timeEntries, tomorrowTasks, slackFormat, teamsFormat
  3. timeEntries total ~28800 seconds (8h)
  4. Issue keys (NARADA-42, 43, 44) are extracted correctly
  5. slackFormat uses Slack mrkdwn, teamsFormat uses Teams markdown

  ## Sample 200 Response

  ```json
  {
    "id": "chatcmpl-...",
    "object": "chat.completion",
    "model": "meta-llama/llama-4-scout-17b-16e-instruct",
    "choices": [
      {
        "index": 0,
        "message": {
          "role": "assistant",
          "content": "{\"tasks\":[{\"description\":\"Groq integration - provider, settings UI, API routes\",\"issueKey\":\"NARADA-42\",\"timeEstimate\":\"3 hours\"},...],\"blockers\":[],\"timeEntries\":[{\"issueKey\":\"NARADA-42\",\"timeSpentSecs\":10800,\"started\":\"2026-04-07T10:00:00.000+05:30\",\"comment\":\"Groq integration\",\"isRepeat\":false},...],\"tomorrowTasks\":[...],\"slackFormat\":\"...\",\"teamsFormat\":\"...\"}"
        },
        "finish_reason": "stop"
      }
    ]
  }
  ```
}
